 to the left and 

00:01:14.415 --> 00:01:17.016
 high concentration of yellow particles on the right. 

00:01:17.016 --> 00:01:20.584
 Their concentration gradient is from right to left. 

00:01:20.584 --> 00:01:22.450
 The purpose of this video is 

00:01:22.450 --> 00:01:25.537
 to show that each particle moves in the direction 

00:01:25.537 --> 00:01:27.606
 of its own concentration gradient. 

00:01:27.606 --> 00:01:29.577
 Unless blocked in any way, 

00:01:29.577 --> 00:01:32.270
 it will move in the direction of its unique concentration gradient, 

00:01:32.270 --> 00:01:34.394
 no matter what they do 

00:01:34.394 --> 00:01:36.252
 other particles. At least for most of the time. 

00:01:36.252 --> 00:01:38.314
 So, we see that the yellow particles will move 

00:01:38.314 --> 00:01:40.988
 from a high place to a low concentration. 

00:01:40.988 --> 00:01:42.312
 They will move 

00:01:42.312 --> 00:01:45.116
 by diffusion from right to left. 

00:01:45.116 --> 00:01:47.746
 This is not magic. 

